The paper proposes a new method for normalizing neural networks based on the Minimum Description Length (MDL) principle, which is commonly used in machine learning and information theory. The paper also applies the method to computer vision and reinforcement learning tasks, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper mentions the compatibility of the proposed method with batch normalization and layer normalization, indicating a potential focus on systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes further research to explore the behaviors among different variants, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
